LOCUS       SNAP_tag                 179 aa            linear   UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  SNAP-tag — ~179-aa self-labeling protein tag engineered by directed
            evolution from human O6-alkylguanine-DNA alkyltransferase
            (hAGT/MGMT); covalently and irreversibly transfers the benzyl group
            of O6-benzylguanine (BG) substrates to its active-site cysteine,
            labeling the fusion protein with the appended probe..
